The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           IN THE CITY
                  
	 Arch-rivals East Bengal and Mohun Bagan will lock horns in the return leg derby of the Sahara CFL Premier Division on September 12 at the Salt Lake Stadium. According to the new fixture released on Monday, the league will be over on September 13 with Mohammedan Sporting taking on Calcutta Port Trust (CPT).             
	THE FIXTURES      
	Sept. 4: Mohun Bagan vs CPT (MB); Sept. 5: East Bengal vs United FC (Salt Lake Stadium); Sept. 8: East Bengal vs Peerless (Salt Lake Stadium); Sept. 9: Mohun Bagan vs Camellia George Telegraph (MB); Sept. 10: Mohammedan Sporting vs CPT (Salt Lake Stadium); Sept. 12: East Bengal vs Mohun Bagan (Salt Lake Stadium); Sept. 13: Mohammedan Sporting vs CPT (Salt Lake Stadium)                
	 East Bengal paddlers were awarded a ONGC Bengal Premier League table tennis match after Mohun Bagan refused to play, protesting against the inclusion of Aman Balgu in the opposition ranks. Bagan alleged that Balgu is ranked 9th in the senior category and cannot be included in category B, the tournament authorities rubbished their claims and awarded the match to East Bengal.                 
	CHESS: The Telegraph Schools Championship, opening ceremony at 3pm at Gorky Sadan                                                                                                                                                                     
